ess your batteries can supply a high amount of current. In our design, the Arduino only sends the control signal to the motor, while the actual power comes from an official battery — the same type that every <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> team already uses.<br>
